.TH VEX 1 "2025" "vex" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vex \- AST-aware diff tool with syntax highlighting and inline editing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vex
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIfile1\fR \fIfile2\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vex
is a modern AST-aware diff tool built with Zig for maximum performance.
It understands the structure of your code, highlighting semantic differences
like moved functions, renamed variables, and modified expressions instead of
meaningless line-by-line changes.
.PP
Key features include:
.IP \(bu 2
AST-aware diff analysis
.IP \(bu 2
Side-by-side and unified diff views
.IP \(bu 2
Syntax highlighting
.IP \(bu 2
Inline editing capabilities
.IP \(bu 2
Git integration
.IP \(bu 2
Large file performance (1MB+ files in under a second)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-side\-by\-side
Display differences in side-by-side mode (default).
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-unified
Display differences in unified diff format.
.TP
.B \-\-ast
Enable AST-aware diff mode for semantic analysis.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable color output.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-context " " \fIN\fR
Number of context lines to show (default: 3).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.BR j ", " \(da
Scroll down
.TP
.BR k ", " \(ua
Scroll up
.TP
.BR Space ", " "Page Down"
Page down
.TP
.BR b ", " "Page Up"
Page up
.TP
.B g
Go to first line
.TP
.B G
Go to last line
.TP
.B n
Jump to next hunk
.TP
.B N
Jump to previous hunk
.SS View Modes
.TP
.B Tab
Toggle side-by-side / unified view
.TP
.B w
Toggle word diff
.TP
.B l
Toggle line numbers
.SS Editing
.TP
.B a
Accept left (old) side
.TP
.B d
Accept right (new) side
.TP
.B e
Enter manual edit mode
.TP
.B u
Undo last change
.TP
.B Ctrl+r
Redo
.SS General
.TP
.B /
Search
.TP
.B ?
Show help
.TP
.B q
Quit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B VEX_THEME
Default color theme (tokyo-night, github-dark, monokai)
.TP
.B VEX_PAGER
Pager program (default: none)
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable colors when set
.SH EXAMPLES
Compare two files:
.PP
.RS
.B vex old_file.txt new_file.txt
.RE
.PP
Side-by-side mode:
.PP
.RS
.B vex -s old.zig new.zig
.RE
.PP
Unified diff with 5 context lines:
.PP
.RS
.B vex -u -c 5 before.js after.js
.RE
.PP
Enable AST-aware mode:
.PP
.RS
.B vex --ast old.py new.py
.RE
.PP
Read from stdin:
.PP
.RS
.B git diff | vex -
.RE
.PP
.SH GIT INTEGRATION
Configure vex as your default diff tool:
.PP
.RS
.B git config --global diff.tool vex
.br
.B git config --global difftool.vex.cmd 'vex "$LOCAL" "$REMOTE"'
.RE
.PP
Then use with:
.PP
.RS
.B git difftool HEAD~3
.RE
